observations.recommendation:
We recommended, and Management agreed, that the City Mayor require the City Accountant to:
a. immediately submit the required supporting documents of the disbursement vouchers identified in Annex A, and to ensure that all pertinent supporting documents are submitted in a regular and timely manner;
b. designate a staff to closely monitor the liquidation of outstanding cash advances;
c. provide manpower assistance to the Assistant City Treasurer in the preparation of liquidation documents of cash advances related to COVID-19 response, and the Confidential and Intelligence fund, to hasten the process;
d. cause the write-off for the outstanding balances of deceased employees and send demand letters to those that were already separated from the service or transferred to another agency.

We recommended, and Management agreed, that the City Mayor direct the:
a. Inventory Committee to create Physical Inventory Plan and be guided with the COA Circular 2020-006;
b. General Services Office to attach property stickers and have a uniform identification system of PPE;
c. City Accountant to properly compute the depreciation expense and reconcile the misclassified accounts.
We likewise reiterate that the Inventory Committee conduct an inventory count, reconcile its report with the records of accounting; and complete the disposal process for unserviceable properties.

We recommended, and Management agreed, that the City Mayor should:
a. strengthen the City’s GFPS by fully capacitating its members through their attendance to various trainings on:
    i. Gender Analysis;
    ii. Gender Planning and Budgeting;
    iii. The use of HGDG, and the Gender Responsive LGUs (GeRL) Ka ba Self-Assessment Tool;
    iv. Gender Sensitivity Issues; and
    v. Other GAD related seminars
b. create a GAD Office, manned by capable personnel who will assist the GFPS in (i) monitoring the City’s compliance with the GAD mandates; and (ii) facilitating the conduct of gender analysis and the preparation of GPB and GAR based on gender analysis and HGDG, including the establishment of relevant sex disaggregated data for both client-focused or agency focused activities proposed in the GPB, among others.
c. ensure that the timelines prescribed by the PCW/DILG in the preparation of GPB are observed so that the DILG reviewed GPB will be incorporated in the Budget Proposal submitted by the City Mayor to the Sanggunian.
d. include the GAD PPAs in the Office Performance Commitment Review of the City and require the inclusion of GAD PPAs in the Division Performance Commitment Review and and Individual Performance Commitment and Review of concerned divisions/personnel.

We reiterated that the City Mayor direct the:
a. General Services Officer and City Accountant to hasten the updating of their records;
b. Inventory Committee to complete the physical count of the properties of the City and reconcile the records of the Property Unit with the Accounting Office and to the error in the computation of depreciation and prepare any adjustments to present accurate PPE account balances;
c. Inventory Committee to complete the physical count of properties as recorded in the report.

We recommended, and Management agreed, that the City Mayor direct the:
a. City Assessor to prepare and submit an updated assessment roll to the City Treasurer to enable the latter to prepare the Real Property Tax /Special Education Tax Assessment Register;
b. City Treasurer and the City Assessor to coordinate with each other for an accurate RPT Account Register;
c. City Treasurer to submit the updated list of RPT at the beginning of the year to the City Accountant.

We recommended and Management agreed, that the City Mayor:
a. Require the General Services Office to:
vi. Secure TCT to support the ownership of the land;
vii. Provide staff and equipment to GSO Personnel concerned in
securing and filing of TCT and other documents;
viii. Reconcile records with the Accounting Office;
ix. Update and submit PCs; and
x. Follow up the sale of unserviceable properties.
