We recommended, and Management agreed, that the City Mayor direct the:
a. City Accountant to reconcile the actual share of the barangays from the RPT collections and to prepare necessary adjusting journal entries;
b. The City Treasurer (i) to release the respective barangay share immediately; and (ii) to release all future barangay shares periodically without the need for action.

We recommended, and Management agreed, that the City Mayor:
a. strengthen the City’s GFPS by fully capacitating its members through
their attendance to various trainings on:
i. Gender Analysis;
ii. GAD Planning and Budgeting;
iii. HGDG;
iv. Gender Responsive LGUs (GeRL) Ka ba;
v. Gender Sensitivity Issues; and
vi. Other GAD related seminars spearheaded by the PCW;
b. create a GAD Office, manned by capable personnel who will assist the
GFPS in (i) monitoring the City’s compliance with the GAD mandates;
and (ii) facilitating the conduct of gender analysis, the preparation of GPB
and GAR based on gender analysis and HGDG, including the
establishment of relevant sex disaggregated data for both client-focused
or agency-focused activities proposed in the GPB, among others;
c. ensure that the timelines prescribed by the PCW/DILG in the preparation
of GPB are observed so that the DILG-reviewed GPB will be incorporated
in the Budget Proposal submitted by the Local Chief Executive to the
Sanggunian; and
d. include the GAD PPAs in the Office Performance Commitment Review of
the City and require the inclusion of GAD PPAs in the Division
Performance Commitment Review and Individual Performance.
Commitment and Review of divisions/personnel concerned.

We recommended that the City Mayor direct the City Accountant:

a. To enforce the immediate liquidation of cash advances and/or require
refund of the unliquidated cash advances by accountable officers;

b. To refrain from granting additional cash advance to officials and
employees until they have fully settled/liquidated the cash advances
previously granted to them;

c. To prepare the necessary adjusting entries on the erroneous account
classification;

d. To designate a staff to closely monitor liquidation of outstanding cash
advances.

7.11 We recommended that Management continue to be compliant with the
terms and conditions of the City’s loan obligations with the lending institutions and
direct the City Accountant to:
a) Reclassify the long term portion in the loans payable;
b) Reconcile the overstatement of the loans payable balances in the FS
and prepare adjusting journal entry, if any;
c) Perform periodic reconciliation of the loans payable account with
respective banks to ensure early detection of unreconciled items and
maintain complete subsidiary ledgers for each loans/borrowings to
record all transactions, particularly releases, repayments and all
charges thereon;
d) Ensure that the Loans Payable are properly disclosed in the Notes to
FS in accordance with the guidelines in the PPSAS;
